<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="about-adv">about <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /əˈbaʊt/    美 /əˈbaʊt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>大约；左右：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s about 10 minutes’ walk. 
步行大约需要10分钟。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>在 / 向周围；四处：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Look about and tell me what you see.
向四周看看，告诉我你看到了什么。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>将近；差不多：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Supper is about ready. 
晚饭快好了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>My stomach is about full.
我差不多饱了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="be-about-to-do-sth">be about to do sth</h3>
<p>1.<strong>正要 / 准备做某事：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I was about to turn off my computer when I received an email. 
我正准备关电脑,这时收到了一封电子邮件。</p><footer>2008 山东</footer></div>

<p>注: be about to常与when连用，表示“刚要…突然…”。  </p>
<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Tom was about to close the window <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ his attention was caught by a bird.  （2010 全国改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. when  </p></div>